in the world am I? Ah, _that's_ the great puzzle!

quoteText:
I'm sure I'm not Ada, for her hair goes in such long
ringlets, and mine doesn't go in ringlets at all; and I'm sure I can't
be Mabel, for I know all sorts of things, and she, oh! she knows such a
very little! Besides, _she's_ she, and _I'm_ I, and--oh dear, how
puzzling it all is! I'll try if I know all the things I used to know.
Let me see: four times five is twelve, and four times six is thirteen,
and four times seven is--oh dear! I shall never get to twenty at that
rate! However, the Multiplication Table doesn't signify: let's try
Geography. London is the capital of Paris, and Paris is the capital of
Rome, and Rome--no, _that's_ all wrong, I'm certain! I must have been
changed for Mabel! I'll try and say '_How doth the little_--'

I'm sure those are not the right words, I must be Mabel after all, and
I shall have to go and live in that poky little house, and have next to

made up my mind about it; if I'm Mabel, I'll stay down here! It'll be
no use their putting their heads down and saying 'Come up again, dear!'
I shall only look up and say 'Who am I then? Tell me that first, and
then, if I like being that person, I'll come up: if not, I'll stay down
here till I'm somebody else'--but, oh dear! I do wish they _would_ put their heads down! I am so
_very_ tired of being all alone here!

that kind of thing never happened, and now here I am in the middle of
one! There ought to be a book written about me, that there ought! And
when I grow up, I'll write one--but I'm grown up now, at least there's no room to grow up any more _here_.

I don't like the look of it at all, however, it may

subQuotationList: ["I don't like the look of it at all,", 'however, it may\nkiss my hand if it likes.']
speaker: The King Of Hearts

quoteText: I'd rather not,
subQuotationList: ["I'd rather not,"]
speaker: The Cat

quoteText:
Don't be impertinent, and don't look at me like
that!
subQuotationList: ["Don't be impertinent,", "and don't look at me like\nthat!"]
speaker: The King Of Hearts

quoteText:
A cat may look at a king, I've read that in some book,
but I don't remember where.
subQuotationList: ['A cat may look at a king,', "I've read that in some book,\nbut I don't remember where."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Well, it must be removed,
subQuotationList: ['Well, it must be removed,']
speaker: The King Of Hearts

quoteText:
My dear! I wish you would
have this cat removed!
subQuotationList: ['My dear! I wish you would\nhave this cat removed!']
speaker: The King Of Hearts

quoteText: Off with his head!
subQuotationList: ['Off with his head!']
speaker: The Queen

quoteText: I'll fetch the executioner myself,
subQuotationList: ["I'll fetch the executioner myself,"]
speaker: The King Of Hearts

quoteText:
but it doesn't
matter much, as all the arches are gone from this side
of the ground.
subQuotationList: ["but it doesn't\nmatter much,", 'as all the arches are gone from this side\nof the ground.']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
It belongs to the
Duchess: you'd better ask _her_ about it.
subQuotationList: ["It belongs to the\nDuchess: you'd better ask _her_ about it."]
speaker: Alice
addressees: ['The Cat', 'The Executioner', 'The King Of Hearts', 'The Queen']
referringExpression: Alice could think of nothing else to say
mentionEntitiesList: [[['The Duchess'], ['The King Of Hearts', 'The Queen'], ['The Duchess']]]

quoteText: She's in prison, fetch her here.
subQuotationList: ["She's in prison,", 'fetch her here.']
speaker: The Queen
referringExpression: the Queen said to the executioner

quoteText: You can't think how glad I am to see you again, you dear old thing!
subQuotationList: ["You can't think how glad I am to see you again, you dear old thing!"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText:
When _I'm_ a Duchess, I won't have any pepper in my kitchen _at all_. Soup
does very well without--Maybe it's always pepper that makes people
hot-tempered, and vinegar that makes them sour--and camomile that makes
them bitter--and--and barley-sugar and such things that make children
sweet-tempered. I only wish people knew _that_: then they wouldn't be
so stingy about it, you know--
subQuotationList:
["When _I'm_ a Duchess,", "I won't have any pepper in my kitchen _at all_. Soup
does very well without--Maybe it's always pepper that makes people
hot-tempered,", "and vinegar that makes them sour--and camomile that makes
them bitter--and--and barley-sugar and such things that make children
sweet-tempered. I only wish people knew _that_: then they wouldn't be
so stingy about it, you know--"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
You're thinking
about something, my dear, and that makes you forget to talk. I can't
tell you just now what the moral of that is, but I shall remember it in
a bit.
subQuotationList:
["You're thinking
about something, my dear, and that makes you forget to talk. I can't
tell you just now what the moral of that is, but I shall remember it in
a bit."]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: Perhaps it hasn't one,
subQuotationList: ["Perhaps it hasn't one,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Tut, tut, child! Everything's got a moral, if only
you can find it.
subQuotationList: ['Tut, tut, child!', "Everything's got a moral, if only\nyou can find it."]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: The game's going on rather better now,
subQuotationList: ["The game's going on rather better now,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
'Tis so, and the moral of that is--'Oh, 'tis love,
'tis love, that makes the world go round!'
subQuotationList: ["'Tis so,", "and the moral of that is--'Oh, 'tis love,\n'tis love, that makes the world go round!'"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText:
Somebody said, that it's done by everybody minding
their own business!
subQuotationList: ['Somebody said,', "that it's done by everybody minding\ntheir own business!"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Ah, well! It means much the same thing, and the moral of
_that_ is--'Take care of the sense, and the sounds will take care of
themselves.'
subQuotationList: ['Ah, well! It means much the same thing,', "and the moral of\n_that_ is--'Take care of the sense, and the sounds will take care of\nthemselves.'"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: How fond she is of finding morals in things!
subQuotationList: ['How fond she is of finding morals in things!']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
I dare say you're wondering why I don't put my arm round your waist, the reason is, that I'm doubtful about
the temper of your flamingo. Shall I try the experiment?
subQuotationList: ["I dare say you're wondering why I don't put my arm round your waist,", "the reason is, that I'm doubtful about\nthe temper of your flamingo. Shall I try the experiment?"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: He might bite,
subQuotationList: ['He might bite,']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Very true, flamingoes and mustard both bite. And
the moral of that is--'Birds of a feather flock together.'
subQuotationList: ['Very true,', "flamingoes and mustard both bite. And\nthe moral of that is--'Birds of a feather flock together.'"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: Only mustard isn't a bird,
subQuotationList: ["Only mustard isn't a bird,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Right, as usual, what a clear way you have of
putting things!
subQuotationList: ['Right, as usual,', 'what a clear way you have of\nputting things!']
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: It's a mineral, I _think_,
subQuotationList: ["It's a mineral, I _think_,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Of course it is, there's a large mustard-mine near here.
And the moral of that is--'The more there is of mine, the less there is
of yours.'
subQuotationList: ['Of course it is,', "there's a large mustard-mine near here.\nAnd the moral of that is--'The more there is of mine, the less there is\nof yours.'"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: Oh, I know! it's a vegetable. It doesn't look like one, but it is.
subQuotationList: ['Oh, I know!', "it's a vegetable. It doesn't look like one, but it is."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
I quite agree with you, and the moral of that
is--'Be what you would seem to be'--or if you'd like it put more
simply--'Never imagine yourself not to be otherwise than what it might
appear to others that what you were or might have been was not
otherwise than what you had been would have appeared to them to be
otherwise.'
subQuotationList:
['I quite agree with you,', "and the moral of that
is--'Be what you would seem to be'--or if you'd like it put more
simply--'Never imagine yourself not to be otherwise than what it might
appear to others that what you were or might have been was not
otherwise than what you had been would have appeared to them to be
otherwise.'"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: I think I should understand that better, if I had it written down: but I can't quite follow it as you say it.
subQuotationList: ['I think I should understand that better,', "if I had it written down: but I can't quite follow it as you say it."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: That's nothing to what I could say if I chose,
subQuotationList: ["That's nothing to what I could say if I chose,"]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: Pray don't trouble yourself to say it any longer than that,
subQuotationList: ["Pray don't trouble yourself to say it any longer than that,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Oh, don't talk about trouble! I make you a present
of everything I've said as yet.
subQuotationList: ["Oh, don't talk about trouble!", "I make you a present\nof everything I've said as yet."]
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText:
A cheap sort of present! I'm glad they don't give
birthday presents like that!
subQuotationList: ['A cheap sort of present!', "I'm glad they don't give\nbirthday presents like that!"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Thinking again?
subQuotationList: ['Thinking again?']
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: I've a right to think,
subQuotationList: ["I've a right to think,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Just about as much right, as pigs have to fly; and
the m--
subQuotationList: ['Just about as much right,', 'as pigs have to fly; and\nthe m--']
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText: A fine day, your Majesty!
subQuotationList: ['A fine day, your Majesty!']
speaker: The Duchess

quoteText:
Now, I give you fair warning, either you or your head must be off, and that in
about half no time! Take your choice!
subQuotationList: ['Now, I give you fair warning,', 'either you or your head must be off, and that in\nabout half no time! Take your choice!']
speaker: The Queen

quoteText: Let's go on with the game,
subQuotationList: ["Let's go on with the game,"]
speaker: The Queen

quoteText:
Off with his head! Off with
her head!
subQuotationList: ['Off with his head!', 'Off with\nher head!']
speaker: The Queen
referringExpression: the Queen never left off quarrelling with the other players and shouting

quoteText:
Have
you seen the Mock Turtle yet?
subQuotationList: ['Have\nyou seen the Mock Turtle yet?']
speaker: The Queen
referringExpression: the Queen left off quite out of breath and said to Alice

quoteText: No, I don't even know what a Mock Turtle is.
subQuotationList: ['No,', "I don't even know what a Mock Turtle is."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: It's the thing Mock Turtle Soup is made from,
subQuotationList: ["It's the thing Mock Turtle Soup is made from,"]
speaker: The Queen

quoteText: I never saw one, or heard of one,
subQuotationList: ['I never saw one, or heard of one,']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Come on, then, and he shall tell you his history,
subQuotationList: ['Come on, then,', 'and he shall tell you his history,']
speaker: The Queen

quoteText: You are all pardoned.
subQuotationList: ['You are all pardoned.']
speaker: The King Of Hearts
referringExpression: the King say in a low voice to the company

quoteText:
Come, _that's_ a
good thing!
subQuotationList: ["Come, _that's_ a\ngood thing!"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Up, lazy
thing! and take this young lady to see the Mock
Turtle, and to hear his history. I must go back and see after some
executions I have ordered;
subQuotationList:
['Up, lazy
thing!', 'and take this young lady to see the Mock
Turtle, and to hear his history. I must go back and see after some
executions I have ordered;']
speaker: The Queen

quoteText: What fun!
subQuotationList: ['What fun!']
speaker: The Gryphon
referringExpression: said the Gryphon half to itself half to Alice

quoteText: What _is_ the fun?
subQuotationList: ['What _is_ the fun?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Why, _she_, It's all her fancy, that: they never
executes nobody, you know. Come on!
subQuotationList: ['Why, _she_,', "It's all her fancy, that: they never\nexecutes nobody, you know. Come on!"]
speaker: The Gryphon
mentionEntitiesList: [[['The Queen']], [['The Queen'], ['The Queen', 'The King Of Hearts', 'The Executioner'], ['Alice']]]

quoteText: Everybody says 'come on!' here, I never was so ordered about in all my life, never!
subQuotationList: ["Everybody says 'come on!' here,", 'I never was so ordered about in all my life, never!']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: What is his sorrow?
subQuotationList: ['What is his sorrow?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
It's all
his fancy, that: he hasn't got no sorrow, you know. Come on!
subQuotationList: ["It's all\nhis fancy, that: he hasn't got no sorrow, you know. Come on!"]
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
This here young lady, she wants for to know your
history, she do.
subQuotationList: ['This here young lady,', 'she wants for to know your\nhistory, she do.']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
I'll tell it her, sit
down, both of you, and don't speak a word till I've finished.
subQuotationList: ["I'll tell it her,", "sit\ndown, both of you, and don't speak a word till I've finished."]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: I don't see how he can _ever_ finish, if he doesn't begin.
subQuotationList: ["I don't see how he can _ever_ finish, if he doesn't begin."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Once, I was a real
Turtle.
subQuotationList: ['Once,', 'I was a real\nTurtle.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Hjckrrh!
subQuotationList: ['Hjckrrh!']
speaker: The Gryphon
referringExpression: broken only by an occasional exclamation of Hjckrrh from the Gryphon

quoteText:
When we were little, we went to school in the
sea. The master was an old Turtle--we used to call him Tortoise--
subQuotationList: ['When we were little,', 'we went to school in the\nsea. The master was an old Turtle--we used to call him Tortoise--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle
mentionEntitiesList: [[['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle']], [['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['Tortoise'], ['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['Tortoise'], ['Tortoise']]]

quoteText: Why did you call him Tortoise, if he wasn't one?
subQuotationList: ["Why did you call him Tortoise, if he wasn't one?"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: We called him Tortoise because he taught us, really you are very dull!
subQuotationList: ['We called him Tortoise because he taught us,', 'really you are very dull!']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText:
You ought to be ashamed of yourself for asking such a simple
question,
subQuotationList: ['You ought to be ashamed of yourself for asking such a simple\nquestion,']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
Drive on, old fellow! Don't be all
day about it!
subQuotationList: ["Drive on, old fellow! Don't be all\nday about it!"]
speaker: The Gryphon
referringExpression: the Gryphon said to the Mock Turtle

quoteText: Yes, we went to school in the sea, though you mayn't believe it--
subQuotationList: ["Yes, we went to school in the sea, though you mayn't believe it--"]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: I never said I didn't!
subQuotationList: ["I never said I didn't!"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: You did,
subQuotationList: ['You did,']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Hold your tongue!
subQuotationList: ['Hold your tongue!']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: We had the best of educations--in fact, we went to school every day--
subQuotationList: ['We had the best of educations--in fact, we went to school every day--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle
mentionEntitiesList: [[['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle']]]

quoteText:
_I've_ been to a day-school, too, you needn't be so
proud as all that.
subQuotationList: ["_I've_ been to a day-school, too,", "you needn't be so\nproud as all that."]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: With extras?
subQuotationList: ['With extras?']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Yes, we learned French and music.
subQuotationList: ['Yes,', 'we learned French and music.']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: And washing?
subQuotationList: ['And washing?']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Certainly not!
subQuotationList: ['Certainly not!']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Ah! then yours wasn't a really good school, Now at _ours_ they had at the end of the bill,
'French, music, _and washing_--extra.'
subQuotationList: ["Ah! then yours wasn't a really good school,", "Now at _ours_ they had at the end of the bill,\n'French, music, _and washing_--extra.'"]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText:
You couldn't have wanted it much, living at the bottom
of the sea.
subQuotationList: ["You couldn't have wanted it much,", 'living at the bottom\nof the sea.']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
I couldn't afford to learn it. I
only took the regular course.
subQuotationList: ["I couldn't afford to learn it.", 'I\nonly took the regular course.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: What was that?
subQuotationList: ['What was that?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Reeling and Writhing, of course, to begin with, and then the different branches of Arithmetic--Ambition,
Distraction, Uglification, and Derision.
subQuotationList: ['Reeling and Writhing, of course, to begin with,', 'and then the different branches of Arithmetic--Ambition,\nDistraction, Uglification, and Derision.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: I never heard of 'Uglification,' What is it?
subQuotationList: ["I never heard of 'Uglification,'", 'What is it?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
What! Never heard of
uglifying! You know what to beautify is, I suppose?
subQuotationList: ['What! Never heard of\nuglifying!', 'You know what to beautify is, I suppose?']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Yes, it means--to--make--anything--prettier.
subQuotationList: ['Yes,', 'it means--to--make--anything--prettier.']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Well, then, if you don't know what to uglify
is, you _are_ a simpleton.
subQuotationList: ['Well, then,', "if you don't know what to uglify\nis, you _are_ a simpleton."]
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: What else had you to learn?
subQuotationList: ['What else had you to learn?']
speaker: Alice
referringExpression: she turned to the Mock Turtle and said

quoteText:
Well, there was Mystery, --Mystery, ancient and modern, with
Seaography: then Drawling--the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,
that used to come once a week: _he_ taught us Drawling, Stretching, and
Fainting in Coils.
subQuotationList:
['Well, there was Mystery,', '--Mystery, ancient and modern, with
Seaography: then Drawling--the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,
that used to come once a week: _he_ taught us Drawling, Stretching, and
Fainting in Coils.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: What was _that_ like?
subQuotationList: ['What was _that_ like?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Well, I can't show it you myself, I'm too
stiff. And the Gryphon never learnt it.
subQuotationList: ["Well, I can't show it you myself,", "I'm too\nstiff. And the Gryphon never learnt it."]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText:
Hadn't time, I went to the Classics master,
though. He was an old crab, _he_ was.
subQuotationList: ["Hadn't time,", 'I went to the Classics master,\nthough. He was an old crab, _he_ was.']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
I never went to him, he taught
Laughing and Grief, they used to say.
subQuotationList: ['I never went to him,', 'he taught\nLaughing and Grief, they used to say.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: So he did, so he did,
subQuotationList: ['So he did, so he did,']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: And how many hours a day did you do lessons?
subQuotationList: ['And how many hours a day did you do lessons?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Ten hours the first day, nine the next, and so
on.
subQuotationList: ['Ten hours the first day,', 'nine the next, and so\non.']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: What a curious plan!
subQuotationList: ['What a curious plan!']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: That's the reason they're called lessons, because they lessen from day to day.
subQuotationList: ["That's the reason they're called lessons,", 'because they lessen from day to day.']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
Then the eleventh day must have been
a holiday?
subQuotationList: ['Then the eleventh day must have been\na holiday?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Of course it was,
subQuotationList: ['Of course it was,']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: And how did you manage on the twelfth?
subQuotationList: ['And how did you manage on the twelfth?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: That's enough about lessons, tell her something about the games now.
subQuotationList: ["That's enough about lessons,", 'tell her something about the games now.']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Same as if he had a bone in his throat,
subQuotationList: ['Same as if he had a bone in his throat,']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: You may not have lived much under the sea--
subQuotationList: ['You may not have lived much under the sea--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: I haven't,
subQuotationList: ["I haven't,"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText: and perhaps you were never even introduced to a lobster--
subQuotationList: ['and perhaps you were never even introduced to a lobster--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: I once tasted--
subQuotationList: ['I once tasted--']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: No, never
subQuotationList: ['No, never']
speaker: Alice
referringExpression: Alice began to say I once tasted but checked herself hastily and said

quoteText:
--so you can have no idea what a delightful thing a
Lobster Quadrille is!
subQuotationList: ['--so you can have no idea what a delightful thing a\nLobster Quadrille is!']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: No, indeed, What sort of a dance is it?
subQuotationList: ['No, indeed,', 'What sort of a dance is it?']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Why, you first form into a line along the
sea-shore--
subQuotationList: ['Why,', 'you first form into a line along the\nsea-shore--']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
Two lines! Seals, turtles, salmon, and so on;
then, when you've cleared all the jelly-fish out of the way--
subQuotationList: ['Two lines!', "Seals, turtles, salmon, and so on;\nthen, when you've cleared all the jelly-fish out of the way--"]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: _That_ generally takes some time,
subQuotationList: ['_That_ generally takes some time,']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: --you advance twice--
subQuotationList: ['--you advance twice--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Each with a lobster as a partner!
subQuotationList: ['Each with a lobster as a partner!']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Of course, advance twice, set to partners--
subQuotationList: ['Of course,', 'advance twice, set to partners--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: --change lobsters, and retire in same order,
subQuotationList: ['--change lobsters, and retire in same order,']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Then, you know, you throw the--
subQuotationList: ['Then, you know,', 'you throw the--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: The lobsters!
subQuotationList: ['The lobsters!']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: --as far out to sea as you can--
subQuotationList: ['--as far out to sea as you can--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Swim after them!
subQuotationList: ['Swim after them!']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Turn a somersault in the sea!
subQuotationList: ['Turn a somersault in the sea!']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Change lobsters again!
subQuotationList: ['Change lobsters again!']
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText: Back to land again, and that's all the first figure,
subQuotationList: ["Back to land again, and that's all the first figure,"]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: It must be a very pretty dance,
subQuotationList: ['It must be a very pretty dance,']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Would you like to see a little of it?
subQuotationList: ['Would you like to see a little of it?']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Very much indeed,
subQuotationList: ['Very much indeed,']
speaker: Alice

quoteText: Come, let's try the first figure! We can do without lobsters, you know. Which shall sing?
subQuotationList: ["Come, let's try the first figure!", 'We can do without lobsters, you know. Which shall sing?']
speaker: The Mock Turtle
referringExpression: said the Mock Turtle to the Gryphon
mentionEntitiesList: [[['The Mock Turtle', 'The Gryphon']], [['The Mock Turtle', 'The Gryphon'], ['The Gryphon']]]

quoteText: Oh, _you_ sing, I've forgotten the words.
subQuotationList: ['Oh, _you_ sing,', "I've forgotten the words."]
speaker: The Gryphon

quoteText:
Thank you, it's a very interesting dance to watch, and I do so like that
curious song about the whiting!
subQuotationList: ["Thank you, it's a very interesting dance to watch,", 'and I do so like that\ncurious song about the whiting!']
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
Oh, as to the whiting, they--you've seen them,
of course?
subQuotationList: ['Oh, as to the whiting,', "they--you've seen them,\nof course?"]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Yes, I've often seen them at dinn--
subQuotationList: ['Yes,', "I've often seen them at dinn--"]
speaker: Alice

quoteText:
I don't know where Dinn may be, but if you've
seen them so often, of course you know what they're like.
subQuotationList: ["I don't know where Dinn may be,", "but if you've\nseen them so often, of course you know what they're like."]
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText:
I believe so, They have their tails in
their mouths--and they're all over crumbs.
subQuotationList: ['I believe so,', "They have their tails in\ntheir mouths--and they're all over crumbs."]
speaker: Alice

subQuotationList: ["You're wrong about the crumbs,", 'crumbs would\nall wash off in the sea. But they _have_ their tails in their mouths;\nand the reason is--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

quoteText: Tell her about the reason and all that,
